main event: Observers in Bradford, Ohio reported sighting an orange-dull white object traveling toward the west for 4-5 minutes.
interesting points: The object was observed at a higher altitude than normal jets and made no sound during the observation., The object's color was described during the sighting as an orange blend with white., The object was considered possibly to be an aircraft., One witness was a 16-year-old male who reported seeing the object with community members., A sketch included in the report depicted the object's motion and estimated size.
sighted object: one orange-dull white object in the sky
